****************** BACKGROUNDS & BORDERS ***************

transparent files:
jpeg they can be transparent
png can be transparent

div is block so if we will set the background it will go across the page

#box-1{
        background-color: coral;
      }

Border has three properties:

    #box-1{
        border-width: 3px;
        border-color: red;
        border-style: solid;
      }
style dotted dashed solid

or just border
border: 3px solid red;

rounding corners
you can choose which corners to round: border-top-left-radius: 10px;

image background
  background-image: url('./img/stars.jpg')


  #box-3{
        background-image: url('./img/stars.jpg');
        color: #fff;
        height: 300px;
        width: 600px
      }

small images repeat to fill the whole page
background-repeat: no-repeat;

background-position: move the image aroung axis x and y
background-position: center center; moving the image around the background
show the whole image
background-size: cover;

using one property
size /cover (slash)

background: url('./img/stars.jpg') no-repeat center center/cover;

fixed backgrounget
bigger it will be cut
fixed when scrolling

browser has default marf=gin and padding
body has margin as well

css reset gets off all of the styling

*{
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
      }

padding is added to the entire width of the thing

to prevent that we need to add a box-sizing property
box-sizing: border-box;

different values per site

everything down overights the up

padding-top: 10px;
padding-right: 20px;
padding-bottom: 10px;
padding-left: 20px;




the same properties


